BFHL REST API

This project implements the BFHL Qualifier REST API as required for the Chitkara University 2026 evaluation.

The application exposes two public endpoints:

GET /health

POST /bfhl

The API is built using Node.js and Express and includes robust input validation, error handling, and external AI integration using Google Gemini.

Live Deployment


Tech Stack

Node.js

Express.js

Google Gemini API

Render (Deployment)

API Endpoints
1. GET /health

Health check endpoint to verify service availability.

Response
{
  "is_success": true,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in"
}

2. POST /bfhl

Accepts exactly one key in the request body and performs the corresponding operation.

Supported Keys
Key	Input Type	Description
fibonacci	Integer	Returns Fibonacci series
prime	Integer Array	Returns only prime numbers
lcm	Integer Array	Returns Least Common Multiple
hcf	Integer Array	Returns Highest Common Factor
AI	String	Returns single-word AI response
Request & Response Examples
Fibonacci

Request

{
  "fibonacci": 7
}


Response

{
  "is_success": true,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in",
  "data": [0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8]
}

Prime Numbers

Request

{
  "prime": [2, 4, 7, 9, 11]
}


Response

{
  "is_success": true,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in",
  "data": [2, 7, 11]
}

LCM

Request

{
  "lcm": [12, 18, 24]
}


Response

{
  "is_success": true,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in",
  "data": 72
}

HCF

Request

{
  "hcf": [24, 36, 60]
}


Response

{
  "is_success": true,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in",
  "data": 12
}

AI Query

Request

{
  "AI": "?"
}


Response

{
  "is_success": true,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in",
  "data": "Mumbai"
}

Error Handling

Only one valid key is allowed per request

Invalid input types return HTTP 400

API never crashes on malformed requests

All error responses follow this format:

{
  "is_success": false,
  "official_email": "shubh3933.beai23@chitkara.edu.in",
  "error": "Error message"
}

Environment Variables

The following environment variable must be set:

GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here


The API key is not hardcoded and is securely injected at runtime.

How to Run Locally
npm install
npm run dev


The server will start on the configured port and expose the APIs locally.

Notes

The repository is public as required

The API is publicly accessible

Input validation and security guardrails are implemented

AI integration uses Google Gemini free tier

